05/04/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The ruling Croatian Democratic Union (HDZ) has taken the lead as local elections approach, according to the results of two separate polls published Tuesday (5 April). 
The surveys were conducted by the Metron and Promocija Plus agencies late last month. 
Metron's poll suggested that HDZ would receive 26 per cent of the vote, followed by the main opposition Social Democratic Party (SDP) with 24.4 per cent. 
Around 20.8 per cent of respondents were undecided. 
The Promocija Plus poll also showed HDZ with a modest lead over SDP. 
Authorities are expected to announce this week the exact date of the local vote. 
(Vjesnik, Dnevnik, Index.hr - 05/04/05)
